<subSubSection id="C36691DBFFACFFA1FF728EAFF036F897" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC3C250FFACFFA1FF728EAFF036F897" blockId="7.[136,787,1251,1883]" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis id="B9081E42FFACFFA1FF728EAFF196FB36" box="[174,229,1252,1275]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">Notes</emphasis>
. – This taxon was mentioned for the first time for the 
<collectingRegion id="49B80CB2FFACFFA1FF548F48F058FAD6" box="[136,299,1283,1307]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDBFA1FFACFFA1FE8D8F48F08DFAD6" author="TAVARES" box="[337,510,1283,1307]" firstAuthor="TAVARES" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" pagination="308 - 391" refId="ref8290" refString="TAVARES, C. N. (1952). Contributions to the lichen flora of Macaronesia. I. Lichens from Madeira. Portugaliae Acta Biol., Ser. B, Sist. 3: 308 - 391." type="journal article" year="1952">TAVARES (1952)</bibRefCitation>
under the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CB9D3FFACFFA1FD6B8F4FF1B2FAF6" authority="Stirt." authorityName="Stirt." class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Usnea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="mollis">
<emphasis id="B9081E42FFACFFA1FD6B8F4FF261FAD6" box="[695,786,1283,1307]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">U. mollis</emphasis>
Stirt.
</taxonomicName>
, a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CB9D3FFACFFA1FEB98F6FF3EEFAF6" authority="(CLERC, 1987)" baseAuthorityName="CLERC" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[357,669,1315,1339]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Usnea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fragilescens">
<emphasis id="B9081E42FFACFFA1FEB98F6FF084FAF6" box="[357,503,1315,1339]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">U. fragilescens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDBFA1FFACFFA1FDDB8F68F3E5FAF6" author="CLERC" box="[519,662,1315,1339]" firstAuthor="CLERC" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" pagination="479 - 495" refId="ref7441" refString="CLERC, P. (1987). Systematics of the Usnea fragilescens aggregate and its distribution in Scandinavia. Nord. J. Bot. 7: 479 - 495." type="journal article" year="1987">CLERC, 1987</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This indication was then taken up again by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDBFA1FFACFFA1FDD48F08F06FFAB6" author="CHAMPION, C. L. &amp; L. SANCHEZ PINTO" journalOrPublisher="Instituto de Estudio Canarios, Santa Cruz de Tenerife" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" refId="ref7406" refString="CHAMPION, C. L. &amp; L. SANCHEZ PINTO (1978). Catalogo preliminar de los Liquenes de Las Islas Canarias. Instituto de Estudio Canarios, Santa Cruz de Tenerife." title="Catalogo preliminar de los Liquenes de Las Islas Canarias" type="book" year="1978">CHAMPION &amp; SANCHEZ PINTO (1978)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDBFA1FFACFFA1FEFA8F28F085FAB6" author="HAFELLNER" box="[294,502,1379,1403]" firstAuthor="HAFELLNER" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" refId="ref7961" refString="HAFELLNER, J. (1995). A new checklist of lichens and lichenicolous fungi of insular Laurimacaronesia including a lichenological bibliography for the area. Fristchiana 5." type="journal volume" year="1995">HAFELLNER (1995)</bibRefCitation>
and HERNÁNDEZ PADRÓN &amp; PÉREZ-VARGAS (2010), “collected on Tenerife”. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CB9D3FFACFFA1FD0C8FCFF06FFA76" authority="Korb." authorityName="Korb." class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Usnea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis id="B9081E42FFACFFA1FD0C8FCFF1A5FA76" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">Usnea cornuta</emphasis>
Körb.
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CB9D3FFACFFA1FE9E8FEFF311FA76" authority="(Duby) Motyka" authorityName="Motyka" baseAuthorityName="Duby" box="[322,610,1443,1467]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Usnea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="inflata">
<emphasis id="B9081E42FFACFFA1FE9E8FEFF0DBFA76" box="[322,424,1443,1467]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">U. inflata</emphasis>
(Duby) Motyka
</taxonomicName>
) a frequent and variable species was not mentioned for the 
<collectingRegion id="49B80CB2FFACFFA1FD898F88F384FA16" box="[597,759,1475,1499]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
in the report of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDBFA1FFACFFA1FECF8FA8F0CCFA36" author="TAVARES" box="[275,447,1507,1531]" firstAuthor="TAVARES" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" pagination="308 - 391" refId="ref8290" refString="TAVARES, C. N. (1952). Contributions to the lichen flora of Macaronesia. I. Lichens from Madeira. Portugaliae Acta Biol., Ser. B, Sist. 3: 308 - 391." type="journal article" year="1952">TAVARES (1952)</bibRefCitation>
. There is thus a high probability that the species reported as 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CB9D3FFACFFA1FE688C4FF363F9D6" box="[436,528,1539,1563]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Usnea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="mollis">
<emphasis id="B9081E42FFACFFA1FE688C4FF363F9D6" box="[436,528,1539,1563]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">U. mollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDBFA1FFACFFA1FDEA8C48F397F9D6" author="TAVARES" box="[566,740,1539,1563]" firstAuthor="TAVARES" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" pagination="308 - 391" refId="ref8290" refString="TAVARES, C. N. (1952). Contributions to the lichen flora of Macaronesia. I. Lichens from Madeira. Portugaliae Acta Biol., Ser. B, Sist. 3: 308 - 391." type="journal article" year="1952">TAVARES (1952)</bibRefCitation>
was in fact 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CB9D3FFACFFA1FF0E8C6FF04FF9F6" box="[210,316,1572,1595]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Usnea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis id="B9081E42FFACFFA1FF0E8C6FF04FF9F6" box="[210,316,1572,1595]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">U. cornuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. So the report in this paper of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CB9D3FFACFFA1FD5F8C6FF261F9F6" baseAuthorityName="CLERC" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[643,786,1571,1595]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Usnea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fragilescens">
<emphasis id="B9081E42FFACFFA1FD5F8C6FF261F9F6" box="[643,786,1571,1595]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">U. fragilescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on La Gomera is the first credible mention of this species for the 
<collectingRegion id="49B80CB2FFACFFA1FF6C8C28F022F9B6" box="[176,337,1635,1659]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
. One of the specimen 
<emphasis id="B9081E42FFACFFA1FDE18C28F1A7F956" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">(Hernàndez &amp; Pérez 56615)</emphasis>
out of the two collected by Hernàndez &amp; Perez on La Gomera corresponds well to the description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CB9D3FFACFFA1FD5E8CEFF261F976" baseAuthorityName="CLERC" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[642,786,1699,1723]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Usnea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fragilescens">
<emphasis id="B9081E42FFACFFA1FD5E8CEFF261F976" box="[642,786,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">U. fragilescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDBFA1FFACFFA1FF358C88F0F2F916" author="CLERC" box="[233,385,1731,1755]" firstAuthor="CLERC" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" pagination="479 - 495" refId="ref7441" refString="CLERC, P. (1987). Systematics of the Usnea fragilescens aggregate and its distribution in Scandinavia. Nord. J. Bot. 7: 479 - 495." type="journal article" year="1987">CLERC (1987)</bibRefCitation>
with the stictic acid group as medullary substances. The second specimen 
<emphasis id="B9081E42FFACFFA1FDED8CA8F1A5F8D6" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">(Hernàndez &amp; Pérez 56616)</emphasis>
however differs in the presence of thamnolic acid as medullary substance. This constitutes a new chemotype for 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CB9D3FFACFFA1FF548D0FF04DF896" baseAuthorityName="CLERC" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[136,318,1859,1883]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Usnea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fragilescens">
<emphasis id="B9081E42FFACFFA1FF548D0FF04DF896" box="[136,318,1859,1883]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">Usnea fragilescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
